<h2>Tanner</h2>

<p>The Tanner is a neutral player. They hate their job and they want out. The Tanner wins the game by getting lynched. If they are lynched, the game immediately ends.</p>

<h3>Role Type</h3>
<ul>
    <li>The Tanner is seen as a Neutral Party by the Seer.</li>
    <li>The Tanner is not seen as a user of witchcraft.</li>
    <li>The Tanner does not have a night action so will not be seen visiting by the Harlot/Stalker/Familiar.</li>
    <li>The Tanner is not seen as a killer by the Adjudicator.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Notes on the Tanner</h3>
<ul>
    <li>The Tanner only wins if they are lynched, being killed at night does not count.</li>
    <li>The Tanner cannot be recruited by sub-faction leaders (Mason, Inquisition, Illuminati). However, they can be recruited by a Vampire or Vampire Master.</li>
    <li>The Tanner is only used in Speed Games.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Tips for playing Tanner</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Tanners are a danger to the wolves as well as the village. Don't rely on the wolves being happy to bandwagon a vote against you if you are too obvious.</li>
</ul>

